Two children died in a collision on the R45 near Hopefield, while two people were killed on the N1 near Plattekloof on Friday. CAPE TOWN - Four people have died in separate car accidents in the Western Cape this weekend. Two children died in a collision on the R45 near Hopefield, while two people were killed on the N1 near Plattekloof on Friday. Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa said, “The driver who caused the accident fled the scene.”